    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="nar.03460.001.jpg" type="verso"/>
           
            <ab>Nov. 9, 1871.</ab>
            <ab>William McMichael, Esq.</ab>
            <ab>Ass't. Atty General at Court of Claims,</ab>
            <ab>Washington, D. C.</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>I have been urged to direct the dismissal of the appeal in the case of Sheldon W. Wight, <hi rend="underline">vs</hi>. The United States.</ab>
            <ab>Will you report to me an outline of the case, and your judgment upon the propriety of dismissing the appeal, unless such a report has already been made from your office; and in that case please refer me to the report by date.</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully,</ab>
            <ab>A. T. Akerman,</ab>
            <ab>Attorney General.</ab>
            
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">certain report asked.</note>
            
            
            
        </body>
